{{Wireless embedded system |brand=Murata |model=PAC-USWHS002-WF |revision=-2 |fcc_date=06/14/2018 |is_manuf=No |type=module, IoT, |fcc_id=2AIGCWFB003 |cpu1_brand=STMicroelectronics |cpu1_model=STM32F413;ARM A, STM32F413, RHT6, GH262 VQ, CHN GH 639, ST; |cpu1_cspeed=100 |fla1=4 |fla1_brand=Winbond |fla1_model=W25Q32JVZPIQ |wi1_chip1_brand=Murata |wi1_chip1_model=SS7411014;SS7411014, 1DX; |wi1_802dot11_protocols=bgn |wi1_txchains=1 |wi1_rxchains=1 |wi1_sstreams=1 |eth_none=true |flags=Bluetooth LE, |802dot11_protocols=bgn |oui=00:AE:FA, DC:EF:CA }}
Product Description from the Test Report filed with the FCC: :"The PAC-USWHS002-WF-2 WIFI-BLE adapter is the second generation in its series. It wirelessly monitors and controls a MEUS [Mitsubishi Electric United States] HVAC unit via WIFI link. This device communicates wirelessly using either 802.11b/g/n WIFI mode or Bluetooth Smart (i.e. BLE) mode"
"MURATA 801120 REV B COPYRIGHT 2017" is silkscreened on the board in the FCC photos.
Top-side marking for the Winbond W25Q32JVZPIQ is 25Q32JVIQ.
